data.description: Wow! Talk about location! This charming 1911 bungalow on the Historic Registry is steps from OSU and an array of restaurants and shops to enjoy. Gorgeous fir floors, built ins and arched doorways are still true to the era, while the updated kitchen offers modern conveniences while retaining the vintage charm. The basement, converted to a great studio apartment with permits has its own entrance and is perfect as a rental or a home to your favorite student, or perhaps airbnb, you name it.
